body:
This is an almost-duplicate of #17437.

## Repro

1. Create a simple namespaced console application.

    - <details><summary>composer.json</summary>

        ```json
        {
            "name": "foo/bar",
            "require": {
                "yiisoft/yii2": "2.0.42.1"
            },
            "autoload": {
                "psr-4": {
                    "foo\\bar\\": "."
                }
            },
            "repositories": [
                {
                    "type": "composer",
                    "url": "https://asset-packagist.org"
                }
            ]
        }
        ```

        </details>
    - <details><summary>main.php</summary>

        ```php
        #!/usr/bin/env php
        <?php

        use yii\console\controllers\MigrateController;
        use yii\db\Connection;

        require_once __DIR__ . '/vendor/autoload.php';
        require_once __DIR__ . '/vendor/yiisoft/yii2/Yii.php';

        $application = new yii\console\Application([
            'id' => 'foo-bar',
            'basePath' => __DIR__,
            'aliases' => [
                '@foo/bar' => '@app',
            ],
            'components' => [
                'db' => [
                    'class' => Connection::class,
                    'dsn' => "sqlite:foo-bar.db",
                    'charset' => 'utf8',
                ],
            ],
            'controllerMap' => [
                'migrate' => [
                    'class' => MigrateController::class,
                    'migrationNamespaces' => [
                        'foo\bar',
                    ],
                    'migrationPath' => null,
                ],
            ],
        ]);
        exit($application->run());
        ```

        </details>

2. Create a migration that ought to generate from a template, e.g. create table:

    ```sh
    php main.php migrate/create --interactive=0 CreateQuxTable
    ```


### What would you expected to happen?

<details><summary>A migration is generated using the appropriate template (e.g. <code>views/createTableMigration.php</code>).</summary>

```php
<?php

namespace foo\bar;

use yii\db\Migration;

/**
 * Handles the creation of table `{{%qux}}`.
 */
class M210517181920CreateQuxTable extends Migration
{
    /**
     * {@inheritdoc}
     */
    public function safeUp()
    {
        $this->createTable('{{%qux}}', [
            'id' => $this->primaryKey(),
        ]);
    }

    /**
     * {@inheritdoc}
     */
    public function safeDown()
    {
        $this->dropTable('{{%qux}}');
    }
}
```

</details>


### What do you get instead?

<details><summary>Migration is generated using the plain, generic <code>views/migration.php</code> template.</summary>

```php
<?php

namespace foo\bar;

use yii\db\Migration;

/**
 * Class M210517181920CreateQuxTable
 */
class M210517181920CreateQuxTable extends Migration
{
    /**
     * {@inheritdoc}
     */
    public function safeUp()
    {

    }

    /**
     * {@inheritdoc}
     */
    public function safeDown()
    {
        echo "M210517181920CreateQuxTable cannot be reverted.\n";

        return false;
    }

    /*
    // Use up()/down() to run migration code without a transaction.
    public function up()
    {

    }

    public function down()
    {
        echo "M210517181920CreateQuxTable cannot be reverted.\n";

        return false;
    }
    */
}
```

</details>


## Additional info

### Cause

https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/b33f1a7ecb71bef0f2cd1b68f0b770980a8ef39c/framework/console/controllers/MigrateController.php#L410-L412

When `$params['namespace']` is non-empty and there are no backslashes in `$name`,

1. `strrpos($name, '\\')` evaluates to `false` and, when that is +1'ed, PHP ~~sucks~~ silently casts it to integer `0`, and
2. that causes `substr()` to remove the first character from `$name`,
3. which later prevents `preg_match`ing the `$name` to any of the template-able patterns.

Quite the mouthful, but it is what it is.


### Patch

The issue is fully mitigated by checking whether the `$name` does actually contain a backslash before taking a substring of it.

```diff
diff --git a/framework/console/controllers/MigrateController.php b/framework/console/controllers/MigrateController.php
index aa2625ea0..2cd652474 100644
--- a/framework/console/controllers/MigrateController.php
+++ b/framework/console/controllers/MigrateController.php
@@ -407,8 +407,9 @@ class MigrateController extends BaseMigrateController
         $foreignKeys = $parsedFields['foreignKeys'];
 
         $name = $params['name'];
-        if ($params['namespace']) {
-            $name = substr($name, strrpos($name, '\\') + 1);
+        $lastBackslash = strrpos($name, '\\');
+        if ($params['namespace'] && $lastBackslash !== false) {
+            $name = substr($name, $lastBackslash + 1);
         }
 
         $templateFile = $this->templateFile;
```


### Analysis

ISTM the tests don't catch the bug because the logic of

https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/b33f1a7ecb71bef0f2cd1b68f0b770980a8ef39c/framework/console/controllers/BaseMigrateController.php#L682-L688

<details><summary>actually has three execution paths, the last of which is an implied empty `else`,</summary>

```php
if (strpos($name, '\\') !== false) {
    $namespace = substr($name, 0, strrpos($name, '\\'));
    $name = substr($name, strrpos($name, '\\') + 1);
} else {
    if ($this->migrationPath === null) {
        $migrationNamespaces = $this->migrationNamespaces;
        $namespace = array_shift($migrationNamespaces);
    } else {
        // do nothing
    }
}
```

</details>

but only two of those execution paths are tested by https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/b33f1a7ecb71bef0f2cd1b68f0b770980a8ef39c/tests/framework/console/controllers/MigrateControllerTest.php#L110-L119

and the `($this->migrationPath === null)` execution path remains untested.

I can't even the fun you're going to have rethinking tests to cover this.


### Versions

| Q                | A
| ---------------- | ---
| Yii version      | v2.0.42.1
| PHP version      |  7.4.14
| Operating system | Alpine Linux v3.11.7
